text: Preben Fjære Brynemo (born 14 August 1977) is a Norwegian Nordic combined skier. He was born in Porsgrunn and represented the club Sannidal IL. He competed at the 2002 Winter Olympics in Salt Lake City, placing 22nd in the individual competition and 30th in the sprint. ==References== Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Nordic combined skiers at the 2002 Winter Olympics Category:Norwegian male Nordic combined skiers Category:Olympic Nordic combined skiers of Norway Category:People from Kragerø
